    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI have installed neovim on M1 Mac Studio running macOS 26.4.1 (25E253) via `brew install neovim`:\n\n```none\n% nvim --version\nNVIM v0.12.2\nBuild type: Release\nLuaJIT 2.1.1774896198\n```\n\nNeoVIM works fine from my macOS terminal (iterm2), as well as when I ssh from another macOS or Fedora box, but when I ssh in from iPadOS, I get strange behaviors:\n\n * When I use “Prompt 3” ssh client, when I launch NeoVIM on my macOS box, I get an extraneous `+q4D73` (a terminal capability?) visually overlaid the first line of the file that I edit. (Obviously, if I scroll it out of view and back into view, the file is fine. It is just an artifact that is leaking on to the screen.)\n\n * When I use “Blink” ssh client, when I launch NeoVIM, it appears to attempt to perform the last search I did. If I didn’t have a previous search, it says:\n\n    > E486: Pattern not found: E35\n\n    If I actually do a search and then quit and restart NeoVIM, rather than seeing that error message, it repeats that search I performed right before quitting and relaunching NeoVIM.\n\n    When I did `nvim --clean -V20vim.log`, I can see that this E35 error appears right before the `--- Terminal info ---` section of the log (though I'm unclear how a terminal configuration could possibly initiate a search).\n\nFWIW:\n\n 1. Neither of these problems manifest themselves when ssh’ing from either of these two iPadOS clients to a Fedora 44 box running NeoVIM v0.11.6:\n\n    ```none\n    % nvim --version\n    NVIM v0.11.6\n    Build type: RelWithDebInfo\n    LuaJIT 2.1.1767980792\n    ```\n\n 2. The “--- Terminal info ---” section of the log from these two iPadOS ssh clients is the same.\n\n 3. Using `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua` does not affect the behavior. From the iPadOS clients, they both manifest their respective erroneous behavior despite the presence of `-u minimal.lua` parameter.\n  \n 4. I see the same behavior when using these iPadOS ssh clients to a M4 Mac mini running beta macOS 26.5 (25F71).\n\n 5. Using `env -i TERM=ansi-256color \"$(which nvim)\"` also manifested the same behavior in both iPadOS ssh clients.\n\nIt looks like something (that escapes me) about the terminal session when ssh’ing from the iPad is confusing NeoVIM. VIM works fine; the problem is isolated to NeoVIM from these iPadOS ssh clients. And it’s not anything in my `init.vim`, because even when I remove that, the behavior persists.\n\nIf there is any other debugging you want me to do (or share my `-V` log files), please let me know. And if you need me to post separate issues for these two clients, let me know, but they both appear to be manifestations of ssh’ing from iPadOS clients.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\n:q\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n* No spurious output from “Prompt 3”\n* No automatic search from “Blink”\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.2 / Build type: Release / LuaJIT 2.1.1774896198\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nvim 9.2 (2026 Feb 14, compiled Apr 27 2026 17:18:17) works fine\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 26.4.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niPadOS apps “Blink” or “Prompt 3”\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
