            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Bisected the pattern error to 5cbb9d61\n\nBlink doesn't support DSR sequence... That's just sad for a terminal that's trying to charge a yearly subscription fee. I believe it's passing through the `[5n` in the DSR request, so nvim sees those keys when it starts. When it hits `n`, it tries to go to the next pattern, and you get that error about the pattern.\n\nUnfortunately, `NVIM_NOTTYFAST` doesn't fix it in this case because we send out DSR sequences in multiple places (`tui_query_bg_color_noflush` in `tui.c` will still send it, at least).\n\nThis sequence has been around since [at least 1979 as part of ECMA-48](https://wezfurlong.org/ecma48/07-control.html#7223-dsr---device-status-report).\n\nNot really an nvim issue IMO.\n\nEDIT: actually, it does seem to support DSR when I just test it using `printf`, so I'm not sure what the problem is when it's running nvim.",
